name: The Swimmer
description:
Reflecting on her past and how it complicated that thing she loved:

The feel of the sun,
the hug of water,
the chill of submersion

Pure nostalgia was challenged by competition and labor. Those days are over. She now sits at peace, back in the flow. With childlike joy, the swimmer returns to the pool's magical grace.

model: Stephanie Sinn
body paint and photography by Roustan (bodypainter.com)
